Description:
                                                                    construction of pole barns at the Edward Perry Sports Complex built as follows: Two 2 buildings will be 20 ft. wide 36 ft. long and 12 ft. tall to the eave of the building and eight 8 buildings will b>>
construction of pole barns at the Edward Perry Sports Complex built as follows: Two 2 buildings will be 20 ft. wide 36 ft. long and 12 ft. tall to the eave of the building and eight 8 buildings will be 20 ft. wide 12 ft. long and 12 ft. to the eave of the building. Roof material will be 29 ga painted metal attached to 2X6 .06 MCA treated pine perlins 24 inches on center. Trusses are square tube open web style built on 2:12 pitch. All trusses will be bolted to 6X6 .60 CCA-C pressure treated post or galvanized post, both trusses and post will be set 12 ft. on center max. The end of the bar will have 29 ga painted custom rake to cover the exposed 2X6 and a 2X8 .06 MCA treated fascia along the eave of the building. Both gable ends will be left open, unless otherwise stated. All buildings must be signed and sealed by a Registered Engineer to withstand wind loads as per county requirements<<








